dc:subject: Cranium
Undetermined
Paget's Disease
dc:description: Cranium retains LC and RI2-C, and the calotte is loose and itself has a loose piece. Individual was afflicted with osteitis deformans (Paget's disease), with profound effects on the cranial bone. The bone is greatly expanded, porous and weathered-looking bone all over vault, and most alveoli are resorbed.

dc:memberOf.title: Ford Collection, UM Museum of Anthropological Archaeology
